"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"# WebSockets\\n\\nThe Indexer can provide realtime data through its WebSockets endpoint.\\n\\nBelow an example is provided of how to establish a connection and watch realtime **trades** updates. See the full API specification [here](/indexer-client/websockets) for other data feeds.\\n\\n::::steps\\n\\n## Connect\\n\\nTo get realtime updates, we first need to establish a connection with the WebSockets endpoint.\\n\\n:::code-group\\n\\n```python [Python]\\n# The message handler, triggered when a message is received.\\ndef handler(ws: IndexerSocket, message: dict):\\n    print(message)\\n```\\n\\n```typescript [TypeScript]\\n// The message handler, triggered when a message is received.\\nfunction handler(message) {\\n  console.log(message);\\n}\\n// Create a socket.\\nconst mySocket = new SocketClient(\\n  Network.testnet().indexerConfig,\\n  // On-connection callback\\n  () => { console.log('socket opened'); },\\n  // On-disconnection callback\\n  () => { console.log('socket closed'); },\\n  // Message handler\\n  (message) => { handler(message); },\\n  // WebSockets event handler\\n  (event) => { console.error('Encountered error:', event.message); },\\n);\\n// Establish the connection.\\nmySocket.connect();\\n```\\n\\n```rust [Rust]\\n// Establish the connection.\\n// An internal loop is spawned which handles the connection state.\\nlet mut indexer = IndexerClient::new(config.indexer);\\n```\\n\\n:::\\n\\n\\nUpon a successful connection you will receive an initial connection message.\\nThis message maybe abstracted away, depending on the client.\\n\\n:::details[Connection response]\\n```tsx\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"connected\\\",\\n  \\\"connection_id\\\": \\\"004a1efa-21bb-4b19-a2e9-a8ffadd6dc53\\\",\\n  \\\"message_id\\\": 0\\n}\\n```\\n:::\\n\\n## Subscribe\\n\\nAfter a connection is established, you may subscribe to several feeds, containing different types of data.\\nWebSockets include information on __markets__, __trades__, __orders__, __candles__, and __subaccounts__.\\n\\n:::code-group\\n\\n```python [Python]\\n# Modify the `handler()` function.\\n# Subscribe only after a succesful connection.\\ndef handler(ws: IndexerSocket, message: dict):\\n  if message[\\\"type\\\"] == \\\"connected\\\":\\n    # Subscribe.\\n    ws.trades.subscribe(ETH_USD)\\n  print(message)\\n```\\n\\n```typescript [TypeScript]\\n// Modify the `handler()` function.\\n// Subscribe only after a succesful connection.\\nfunction handler(message) {\\n  console.log(message);\\n  if (typeof message.data === 'string') {\\n    const jsonString = message.data as string;\\n    try {\\n      const data = JSON.parse(jsonString);\\n      if (data.type === IncomingMessageTypes.CONNECTED) {\\n        // Subscribe.\\n        mySocket.subscribeToTrades('ETH-USD');\\n      }\\n      console.log(data);\\n    } catch (e) {\\n      console.error('Error parsing JSON message:', e);\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n```rust [Rust]\\n// Subscribe.\\nlet trades_feed = indexer.feed().trades(&\\\"ETH-USD\\\", false).await?;\\n```\\n:::\\n\\n## Handling the data\\n\\nAfter subscription, you will start receiving the update messages.\\nHere, the update messages contain the finalized trades (matched orders) for the `ETH-USD` ticker.\\n\\nFor each received message, the `handler()` function will be called on it. Modify it to implement your desired logic.\\n\\n:::details[Handling in Rust]\\nIn Rust, callbacks are not used. Intead, the handle returned on subscription must be polled.\\n\\n```rust [Rust]\\n// Continuous loop running until the feed is stopped.\\nwhile let Some(msg) = trades_feed.recv().await {\\n    println!(\\\"New trades update: {msg:?}\\\");\\n}\\n```\\n:::\\n\\n## Unsubscribe\\n\\nWhen the data feed is not needed anymore, you may stop it and unsubscribe from it.\\n\\n:::code-group\\n\\n```python [Python]\\nws.trades.unsubscribe(ETH_USD)\\n```\\n\\n```typescript [TypeScript]\\nmySocket.unsubscribeFromTrades('ETH-USD');\\n```\\n\\n```rust [Rust]\\n// To unsubscribe, drop the feed handle (here `trades_feed`).\\n```\\n\\n:::\\n::::\\n\\n## Details\\n\\n### Rate Limiting\\n\\nThe default rate limiting config for WebSockets is:\\n- 2 subscriptions per (connection + channel + channel ID) per second.\\n- 2 invalid messages per connection per second.\\n\\n### Maintaining a Connection\\n\\nEvery 30 seconds, the WebSockets API will send a [heartbeat `ping` control frame](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSockets_API/Writing_WebSocket_servers#pings_and_pongs_the_heartbeat_of_websockets) to the connected client.\\nIf a `pong` event is not received within 10 seconds back, the websocket API will disconnect.\\n\\n### CLI example\\n\\nYou can use a command-line WebSockets client such as [`interactive-websocket-cli`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/interactive-websocket-cli) to connect and subscribe to channels.\\n\\nExample (with `interactive-websocket-cli`):\\n\\n```tsx\\n# For the deployment by DYDX token holders (mainnet), use\\n# wscli connect wss://indexer.dydx.trade/v4/ws\\nwscli connect wss://indexer.v4testnet.dydx.exchange/v4/ws\\n<output from ws-cli>\\n<type 's' to send> { \\\"type\\\": \\\"subscribe\\\", \\\"channel\\\": \\\"v4_trades\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"BTC-USD\\\" }\\n```\\n\\n\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/interaction/data/feeds#websockets\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n<p>The Indexer can provide realtime data through its WebSockets endpoint.</p>\\n<p>Below an example is provided of how to establish a connection and watch realtime <strong>trades</strong> updates. See the full API specification <a href=\\\"/indexer-client/websockets\\\">here</a> for other data feeds.</p>\\n<div data-vocs-steps=\\\"true\\\"><div data-depth=\\\"2\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/data/feeds.mdx#websockets\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\nThe Indexer can provide realtime data through its WebSockets endpoint.\\nBelow an example is provided of how to establish a connection and watch realtime trades updates. See the full API specification here for other data feeds.\\n\",\"title\":\"WebSockets\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/data/feeds#connect\",\"html\":\"<p>To get realtime updates, we first need to establish a connection with the WebSockets endpoint.</p><div class=\\\"code-group\\\"><div data-title=\\\"Python\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Python\\\" data-lang=\\\"python\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\"># The message handler, triggered when a message is received.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">def</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\"> handler</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(ws: IndexerSocket, message: </span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">dict</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">):</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">    print</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(message)</span></span></code></pre></div><div data-title=\\\"TypeScript\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"TypeScript\\\" data-lang=\\\"typescript\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">// The message handler, triggered when a message is received.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">function</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\"> handler</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#E36209;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">message</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">) {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">  console.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">log</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(message);</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">}</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">// Create a socket.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">const</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> mySocket</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> =</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> new</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\"> SocketClient</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">  Network.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">testnet</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">().indexerConfig,</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">  // On-connection callback</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">  () </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=&gt;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> { console.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">log</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&#x27;socket opened&#x27;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">); },</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">  // On-disconnection callback</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">  () </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=&gt;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> { console.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">log</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&#x27;socket closed&#x27;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">); },</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">  // Message handler</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">  (</span><span style=\\\"color:#E36209;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">message</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">) </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=&gt;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> { </span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">handler</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(message); },</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">  // WebSockets event handler</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">  (</span><span style=\\\"color:#E36209;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">event</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">) </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=&gt;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> { console.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">error</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&#x27;Encountered error:&#x27;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">, event.message); },</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">);</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">// Establish the connection.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">mySocket.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">connect</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">();</span></span></code></pre></div><div data-title=\\\"Rust\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Rust\\\" data-lang=\\\"rust\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">// Establish the connection.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">// An internal loop is spawned which handles the connection state.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">let</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> mut</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> indexer </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\"> IndexerClient</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">::</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">new</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(config</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">.</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">indexer);</span></span></code></pre></div></div><p>Upon a successful connection you will receive an initial connection message.\\nThis message maybe abstracted away, depending on the client.</p><details><summary>Connection response</summary><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">{</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">  &quot;type&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;connected&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">,</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">  &quot;connection_id&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;004a1efa-21bb-4b19-a2e9-a8ffadd6dc53&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">,</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">  &quot;message_id&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">0</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">}</span></span></code></pre></details></div><div data-depth=\\\"2\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/data/feeds.mdx#connect\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"To get realtime updates, we first need to establish a connection with the WebSockets endpoint.# The message handler, triggered when a message is received.\\ndef handler(ws: IndexerSocket, message: dict):\\n    print(message)// The message handler, triggered when a message is received.\\nfunction handler(message) {\\n  console.log(message);\\n}\\n// Create a socket.\\nconst mySocket = new SocketClient(\\n  Network.testnet().indexerConfig,\\n  // On-connection callback\\n  () =&gt; { console.log(&#x27;socket opened&#x27;); },\\n  // On-disconnection callback\\n  () =&gt; { console.log(&#x27;socket closed&#x27;); },\\n  // Message handler\\n  (message) =&gt; { handler(message); },\\n  // WebSockets event handler\\n  (event) =&gt; { console.error(&#x27;Encountered error:&#x27;, event.message); },\\n);\\n// Establish the connection.\\nmySocket.connect();// Establish the connection.\\n// An internal loop is spawned which handles the connection state.\\nlet mut indexer = IndexerClient::new(config.indexer);Upon a successful connection you will receive an initial connection message.\\nThis message maybe abstracted away, depending on the client.Connection response{\\n  &quot;type&quot;: &quot;connected&quot;,\\n  &quot;connection_id&quot;: &quot;004a1efa-21bb-4b19-a2e9-a8ffadd6dc53&quot;,\\n  &quot;message_id&quot;: 0\\n}\",\"title\":\"Connect\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/data/feeds#subscribe\",\"html\":\"<p>After a connection is established, you may subscribe to several feeds, containing different types of data.\\nWebSockets include information on <strong>markets</strong>, <strong>trades</strong>, <strong>orders</strong>, <strong>candles</strong>, and <strong>subaccounts</strong>.</p><div class=\\\"code-group\\\"><div data-title=\\\"Python\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Python\\\" data-lang=\\\"python\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\"># Modify the `handler()` function.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\"># Subscribe only after a succesful connection.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">def</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\"> handler</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(ws: IndexerSocket, message: </span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">dict</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">):</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">  if</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> message[</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;type&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">] </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">==</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> &quot;connected&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">:</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">    # Subscribe.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">    ws.trades.subscribe(</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">ETH_USD</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">)</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">  print</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(message)</span></span></code></pre></div><div data-title=\\\"TypeScript\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"TypeScript\\\" data-lang=\\\"typescript\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">// Modify the `handler()` function.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">// Subscribe only after a succesful connection.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">function</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\"> handler</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#E36209;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">message</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">) {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">  console.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">log</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(message);</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">  if</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> (</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">typeof</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> message.data </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">===</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> &#x27;string&#x27;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">) {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">    const</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> jsonString</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> =</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> message.data </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">as</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> string</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">;</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">    try</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">      const</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> data</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> =</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> JSON</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">parse</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(jsonString);</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">      if</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> (data.type </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">===</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> IncomingMessageTypes.</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">CONNECTED</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">) {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">        // Subscribe.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">        mySocket.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">subscribeToTrades</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&#x27;ETH-USD&#x27;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">);</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">      }</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">      console.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">log</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(data);</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">    } </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">catch</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> (e) {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">      console.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">error</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&#x27;Error parsing JSON message:&#x27;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">, e);</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">    }</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">  }</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">}</span></span></code></pre></div><div data-title=\\\"Rust\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Rust\\\" data-lang=\\\"rust\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">// Subscribe.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">let</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> trades_feed </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> indexer</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">feed</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">()</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">trades</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">&amp;</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;ETH-USD&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">, </span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">false</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">)</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">.await?</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">;</span></span></code></pre></div></div></div><div data-depth=\\\"2\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/data/feeds.mdx#subscribe\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"After a connection is established, you may subscribe to several feeds, containing different types of data.\\nWebSockets include information on markets, trades, orders, candles, and subaccounts.# Modify the `handler()` function.\\n# Subscribe only after a succesful connection.\\ndef handler(ws: IndexerSocket, message: dict):\\n  if message[&quot;type&quot;] == &quot;connected&quot;:\\n    # Subscribe.\\n    ws.trades.subscribe(ETH_USD)\\n  print(message)// Modify the `handler()` function.\\n// Subscribe only after a succesful connection.\\nfunction handler(message) {\\n  console.log(message);\\n  if (typeof message.data === &#x27;string&#x27;) {\\n    const jsonString = message.data as string;\\n    try {\\n      const data = JSON.parse(jsonString);\\n      if (data.type === IncomingMessageTypes.CONNECTED) {\\n        // Subscribe.\\n        mySocket.subscribeToTrades(&#x27;ETH-USD&#x27;);\\n      }\\n      console.log(data);\\n    } catch (e) {\\n      console.error(&#x27;Error parsing JSON message:&#x27;, e);\\n    }\\n  }\\n}// Subscribe.\\nlet trades_feed = indexer.feed().trades(&amp;&quot;ETH-USD&quot;, false).await?;\",\"title\":\"Subscribe\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/data/feeds#handling-the-data\",\"html\":\"<p>After subscription, you will start receiving the update messages.\\nHere, the update messages contain the finalized trades (matched orders) for the <code>ETH-USD</code> ticker.</p><p>For each received message, the <code>handler()</code> function will be called on it. Modify it to implement your desired logic.</p><details><summary>Handling in Rust</summary><p>In Rust, callbacks are not used. Intead, the handle returned on subscription must be polled.</p><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Rust\\\" data-lang=\\\"rust\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">// Continuous loop running until the feed is stopped.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">while</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> let</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\"> Some</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(msg) </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> trades_feed</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">recv</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">()</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">.await</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">    println!</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;New trades update: {msg:?}&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">);</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">}</span></span></code></pre></details></div><div data-depth=\\\"2\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/data/feeds.mdx#handling-the-data\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"After subscription, you will start receiving the update messages.\\nHere, the update messages contain the finalized trades (matched orders) for the ETH-USD ticker.For each received message, the handler() function will be called on it. Modify it to implement your desired logic.Handling in RustIn Rust, callbacks are not used. Intead, the handle returned on subscription must be polled.// Continuous loop running until the feed is stopped.\\nwhile let Some(msg) = trades_feed.recv().await {\\n    println!(&quot;New trades update: {msg:?}&quot;);\\n}\",\"title\":\"Handling the data\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/data/feeds#unsubscribe\",\"html\":\"<p>When the data feed is not needed anymore, you may stop it and unsubscribe from it.</p><div class=\\\"code-group\\\"><div data-title=\\\"Python\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Python\\\" data-lang=\\\"python\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">ws.trades.unsubscribe(</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">ETH_USD</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">)</span></span></code></pre></div><div data-title=\\\"TypeScript\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"TypeScript\\\" data-lang=\\\"typescript\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">mySocket.</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">unsubscribeFromTrades</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">(</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&#x27;ETH-USD&#x27;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">);</span></span></code></pre></div><div data-title=\\\"Rust\\\"><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Rust\\\" data-lang=\\\"rust\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">// To unsubscribe, drop the feed handle (here `trades_feed`).</span></span></code></pre></div></div></div></div>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/data/feeds.mdx#unsubscribe\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"When the data feed is not needed anymore, you may stop it and unsubscribe from it.ws.trades.unsubscribe(ETH_USD)mySocket.unsubscribeFromTrades(&#x27;ETH-USD&#x27;);// To unsubscribe, drop the feed handle (here `trades_feed`).\\n\",\"title\":\"Unsubscribe\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/data/feeds#details\",\"html\":\"\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/data/feeds.mdx#details\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\",\"title\":\"Details\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/data/feeds#rate-limiting\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>The default rate limiting config for WebSockets is:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>2 subscriptions per (connection + channel + channel ID) per second.</li>\\n<li>2 invalid messages per connection per second.</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/data/feeds.mdx#rate-limiting\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nThe default rate limiting config for WebSockets is:\\n\\n2 subscriptions per (connection + channel + channel ID) per second.\\n2 invalid messages per connection per second.\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Rate Limiting\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets\",\"Details\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/data/feeds#maintaining-a-connection\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Every 30 seconds, the WebSockets API will send a <a href=\\\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebSockets_API/Writing_WebSocket_servers#pings_and_pongs_the_heartbeat_of_websockets\\\">heartbeat <code>ping</code> control frame</a> to the connected client.\\nIf a <code>pong</code> event is not received within 10 seconds back, the websocket API will disconnect.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/data/feeds.mdx#maintaining-a-connection\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nEvery 30 seconds, the WebSockets API will send a heartbeat ping control frame to the connected client.\\nIf a pong event is not received within 10 seconds back, the websocket API will disconnect.\\n\",\"title\":\"Maintaining a Connection\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets\",\"Details\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/data/feeds#cli-example\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>You can use a command-line WebSockets client such as <a href=\\\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/interactive-websocket-cli\\\"><code>interactive-websocket-cli</code></a> to connect and subscribe to channels.</p>\\n<p>Example (with <code>interactive-websocket-cli</code>):</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"># For the deployment by </span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">DYDX</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> token </span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\\\">holders</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> (mainnet), use</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"># wscli connect </span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">wss</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">:</span><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">//indexer.dydx.trade/v4/ws</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">wscli connect </span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">wss</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">:</span><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">//indexer.v4testnet.dydx.exchange/v4/ws</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">&lt;</span><span style=\\\"color:#22863A;--shiki-dark:#8DDB8C\\\">output</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> from</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> ws-cli</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">&gt;</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">&lt;</span><span style=\\\"color:#22863A;--shiki-dark:#8DDB8C\\\">type</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> &#x27;s&#x27;</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> to</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> send</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">&gt; </span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">{</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> &quot;type&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;subscribe&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">, </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;channel&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;v4_trades&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">, </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;id&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;BTC-USD&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> }</span></span></code></pre>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/data/feeds.mdx#cli-example\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nYou can use a command-line WebSockets client such as interactive-websocket-cli to connect and subscribe to channels.\\nExample (with interactive-websocket-cli):\\n# For the deployment by DYDX token holders (mainnet), use\\n# wscli connect wss://indexer.dydx.trade/v4/ws\\nwscli connect wss://indexer.v4testnet.dydx.exchange/v4/ws\\n&lt;output from ws-cli&gt;\\n&lt;type &#x27;s&#x27; to send&gt; { &quot;type&quot;: &quot;subscribe&quot;, &quot;channel&quot;: &quot;v4_trades&quot;, &quot;id&quot;: &quot;BTC-USD&quot; }\",\"title\":\"CLI example\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets\",\"Details\"]}]}}"
